## Part 6 — Each File Explained

### 📄 pom.xml — The Shopping List

Before you cook a meal, you need ingredients. Before your app runs, it needs libraries. `pom.xml` is that list.

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

This is like saying "I need the web server ingredient." Maven (the build tool) reads this file and automatically downloads everything from the internet the first time you run the project.

Key dependencies we use:

```
spring-boot-starter-web        → Makes it a web application (handles HTTP requests)
spring-boot-starter-data-jpa   → Talks to the database
spring-boot-starter-security   → Handles authentication/JWT
spring-boot-starter-validation → Validates input data
mysql-connector-j              → MySQL database driver
springdoc-openapi              → Generates Swagger UI
lombok                         → Reduces repetitive code
jjwt                           → JWT token library
```

