### 📄 application.properties — The Settings File

This is the **configuration file**. It tells your app how to behave.

```properties
server.port=8081
```
This service runs on port 8081. Like an apartment number — other services live on 8082, 8083, 8084.

```properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/item_db
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=root
```
This is the **address and login** for your MySQL database. Like a home address + key to get in.

```properties
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
```
This tells Hibernate (the database tool): "Look at my Java classes and automatically create/update the database tables." You don't have to write `CREATE TABLE` SQL yourself.

```properties
jwt.secret=ecommerce-item-service-secret-key-for-jwt-auth-2025
jwt.expiration=86400000
```
The secret key used to sign JWT tokens, and expiration time (86400000 milliseconds = 24 hours).

