## Part 9 — The 4 Databases

Each service has its **own completely separate database**. They don't share data.

```
item_db
└── items table
    (id, name, description, category, created_at)

inventory_db
└── inventory table
    (id, item_id, quantity, warehouse_location, last_updated)

notification_db
└── notifications table
    (id, event_type, recipient, message, sent_at)

audit_db
└── audit_logs table
    (id, service_name, operation, record_id, timestamp, details)
```

Notice that `inventory` has an `item_id` column — this is a **logical reference** to an item. In a real production system, services would call each other's APIs to get related data.

